  "text": "The ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) gRPC server implementation in Envoy v1.31.2 is distributed across two main directories:\n\n## Core gRPC Stream Handler (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/)\n\nThe **GrpcStream** class (grpc_stream.h) implements the low-level gRPC stream handling, managing bidirectional gRPC communication with backoff retry logic, rate limiting, and stream establishment/closure. It implements Grpc::AsyncStreamCallbacks and dispatches incoming DiscoveryResponse messages to the mux layer.\n\n## Legacy Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/)\n\nThe legacy implementation includes **GrpcMuxImpl** (grpc_mux_impl.h/cc) which manages subscriptions and multiplexes multiple resource types on a single ADS stream. The legacy delta-xDS variant tracks **DeltaSubscriptionState** (delta_subscription_state.h/cc), handling per-resource versioning and incremental updates. The legacy subscription layer (**GrpcSubscriptionImpl**, grpc_subscription_impl.h/cc) provides subscription management with factory patterns (grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc, grpc_collection_subscription_factory.h/cc).\n\n## New Unified Mux Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/)\n\nThe newer unified implementation provides template-based generic mux management with:\n\n- **GrpcMuxImpl** template (grpc_mux_impl.h/cc) - Generic mux managing subscriptions and request queuing\n- **GrpcMuxDelta** - Delta-xDS specialization of GrpcMuxImpl\n- **GrpcMuxSotw** - State-of-the-world (SotW) xDS specialization\n- **BaseSubscriptionState** template (subscription_state.h) - Base protocol state tracker with ACK/NACK handling via **UpdateAck** struct\n- **DeltaSubscriptionState** (delta_subscription_state.h/cc) - Tracks delta-xDS protocol state with per-resource version tracking (ResourceState) and incremental updates (names_added_, names_removed_)\n- **SotwSubscriptionState** (sotw_subscription_state.h/cc) - Tracks state-of-the-world protocol state with full resource set management and version_info tracking\n- **DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory** and **SotwSubscriptionStateFactory** - Create appropriate subscription state instances\n\n## Resource Subscription and ACK/NACK Processing\n\nResource subscription tracking is managed through:\n\n- **WatchMap** (watch_map.h/cc) - Maps resource name watches to subscription callbacks\n- **PausableAckQueue** (pausable_ack_queue.h/cc) - Queues ACKs/NACKs with pause/resume capability for ordered delivery\n- **UpdateAck** struct (update_ack.h) - Carries nonce, type_url, and error_detail for ACK/NACK handling\n\nThe ACK/NACK mechanism works by:\n1. BaseSubscriptionState::handleResponse() copies the response nonce and marks errors in UpdateAck\n2. getNextRequestWithAck() includes the nonce (ACK) and optional error_detail (NACK) in the next DiscoveryRequest\n3. handleBadResponse() sets error_detail.code to Internal when validation fails, triggering a NACK\n\n## Additional Support Components\n\n- **GrpcMuxContext** (grpc_mux_context.h) - Configuration context for mux creation\n- **GrpcMuxFailover** (grpc_mux_failover.h) - Failover support for primary/secondary xDS sources\n- **EdsResourcesCacheImpl** (eds_resources_cache_impl.h/cc) - Caches EDS resources for optimization\n- **XdsSourceId** (xds_source_id.h/cc) - Tracks xDS source identification\n- **NewGrpcMuxImpl** (new_grpc_mux_impl.h/cc) - Intermediate mux variant for migration\n\nThis architecture separates concerns: the GrpcStream handles transport-level gRPC operations, the mux manages resource subscriptions and request queuing, subscription states track protocol state and ACK/NACK logic, and the watch map manages application-level resource interest callbacks."
}

